  "prompt": "What causes a pulsating feeling under the left rib cage?",
  "response": "Several conditions can cause a pulsating feeling under the left rib cage:\n\n1. Cardiac-related causes\n- Heart palpitations\n- Mitral valve prolapse\n- Arrhythmia\n- Anxiety or stress\n\n2. Digestive system issues\n- Gastritis\n- Irritable bowel syndrome\n- Gas or bloating\n- Spleen enlargement\n\n3. Muscle and skeletal reasons\n- Muscle strain\n- Intercostal muscle spasms\n- Rib injury\n\n4. Vascular conditions\n- Aortic aneurysm\n- Blood vessel inflammation\n- Enlarged blood vessels\n\n5. Neurological factors\n- Nerve compression\n- Nerve irritation\n\n6. Other potential causes\n- Costochondritis (chest wall inflammation)\n- Kidney problems\n- Anxiety or panic attacks\n\nImportant recommendations:\n- If the sensation is persistent or accompanied by pain\n- If you experience chest pain, shortness of breath, or dizziness\n- If the pulsing is severe or worsening\n\nConsult a healthcare professional for proper diagnosis and treatment. They can perform necessary examinations to determine the underlying cause.",
